                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The proposed approach relies on using exclusively audio signals captured within the beehive. This noninvasive solution enables continuous monitoring of the beehive, without disturbing the bees or altering their natural behavior. It can provide valuable information for beekeepers, researchers, or conservationists, helping them make informed decisions about hive "
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "bbox": [
                                1252,
                                1062,
                                2301,
                                1656
                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "management, health assessments, or interventions if necessary. The sound level amplitude and frequency depend on the colony activity and health state. Flying bees produce a typical sound with an approximate frequency of "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "250\\mathrm{Hz}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " worker bees produce a characteristic frequency that lies between 225 and "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "285\\mathrm{Hz}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " to cool the hive with ventilation, and the frequency can reach up to "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "3000\\mathrm{Hz}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1252,
                                        1062,
                                        2301,
                                        1656
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " as a defensive reaction to potential outside threats to the colony [26], [27]. However, if the queen is missing in the beehive the bees produce a sound that contains harmonics with lower frequencies [28]. Fig. 1 reports the schematic representation of the methodology adopted in this study, details of all steps will be given in the following sections."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
